rice paid– external observers generally state that only a small part of the writeoff appears to be due to accounting misstatements and that hp had overpaid for businesses previously hp recruited robert youngjohns exmicrosoft president of north america to take over hp autonomy in september  and since that time has worked towards a turnaround through expanding its information management and analytics software business though the company is integrating into hp software autonomy remains a singular operational business in  hp agreed to sell its autonomy assets as part of a wider deal to the british software company micro focus contents  history  inception and expansion  hewlett packard  products and services  haven big data platform  offices  see also  references  external links historyedit inception and expansionedit autonomy was founded in cambridge england by michael lynch david tabizel and richard gaunt in  as a spinoff from cambridge neurodynamics a firm specializing in computerbased finger print recognition autonomy floated in  on the nasdaq exchange at a share price of approximately £ at the height of the dot com bubble the peak share price was £ december  autonomy acquired verity inc one of its main competitors for approximately us million in  autonomy also acquired neurodynamics may  after exercising an option to buy a stake in technology start up blinkx inc and combining it with its consumer division autonomy floated blinkx on a valuation of  million july  autonomy acquired zantaz an email archiving and litigation support company for  million october  autonomy acquired meridio holdings ltd a uk company based in northern ireland that specialised in records management software for £ million  may  kainos extended its partnership with autonomy for highend information processing and information risk management irm to deliver information governance solutions to its customer base january  autonomy acquired interwoven a niche provider of enterprise content management s