ekers bid to remake the company into an enterprise software powerhouse related hp says its working to bring autonomy products to channel he fills a post that has been vacant since may when hp fired autonomy cofounder and ceo mike lynch after secondquarter license revenue results that ceo meg whitman described as disappointing although hp assigned a channel chief for autonomy in july the company is still not selling autonomy products through the channel in the meantime hp partners are getting restless fielding customer inquiries but lacking the enablement from hp to turn them into business intelligent data operating layer idol a search and data processing technology that is built into many autonomy products and available as a standalone server is regarded as the most valuable asset hp gained from its acquisition idol manages socalled unstructured data such as that found in emails voice video and social media posts the volume of which is growing quickly in businesses youngjohns joined microsoft in  and was president of the software giants north america business prior to being hired by hp he previously spent  years at sun microsystems and  years at ibm he holds an ma in physics and philosophy from the university of oxford published sept   printerfriendly version email this crn article slide shows  companies that had a rough weekfor the week ending july  crn looks at it companies that were unfortunate unsuccessful or just didnt make good decisions vmware executives talk joint certifications with aws getting cozy with microsoft and the next phase for airwatchvmwares frank rauch and airwatchs paul ford discuss how the companys adversarial relationships with aws and microsoft are coming to an end  companies that came to win this weekfor the week ending july  crn takes a look at the companies that brought their a game to the channel more slide shows search videos red hat launches new boston location provides handson experience for customersred hat technologies recently laun